default1.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe are concerned that system performance should be viewed as a whole rather than concentrating on the primary fuel emissions
default.  
defaultWhatever analysis structure is implemented it should always centre on minimising the energy use at point of delivery and also the energy consumed in the systems that then deliver the energy.
default1.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs buildings become more energy efficient through the application of insulation and control of air infiltration, the energy used in the delivery systems can be as much as 40% of the total energy delivered
default.  
defaultThis auxiliary energy is invariably electricity with its high CO
default2
default content.
default1.5
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
