default2.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIs the 
defaultGovernment
default taking the right approach to reduce heat energy demand
default?
defaultJust as people in business or in their homes do not wake up and ask themselves, “
defaulthow much en
defaultergy can we  save today
default?”, so they do not value heat until they do not have it
default.  
defaultTheir main awareness comes when a large utility bill arrives on the doorstep
default.  
defaultAs the production of heat for space heating is seldom of strategic financial importance to people, it attracts little attention except in those areas where there is a major impact
default,
default eg in buildings such as hospitals and universities
default.  
defaultThere are few significant drivers for change and almost always competing
default investment opportunities.
defaultIn 
defaultGovernment
default, responsibility for energy demand falls between 
defaultthree dep
defaultartments
default:
default(a)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
